  "text": "Audit findings for Chromium renderer process sandbox implementation:\n\n1. **BPFBasePolicy (Linux seccomp-BPF base policy)**: Implemented in `sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_base_policy_linux.cc` and declared in `sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_base_policy_linux.h`. The class `BPFBasePolicy` inherits from `bpf_dsl::Policy` and implements `EvaluateSyscall()` and `InvalidSyscall()`. All other Linux BPF policies (renderer, GPU, audio, CDM, etc.) inherit from this base class. It internally composes a `BaselinePolicy` from the lower-level sandbox library.\n\n2. **TargetPolicy (Windows sandbox policy)**: Defined in `sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy.h`. The class `TargetPolicy` (line 263) is the primary interface for configuring the Windows sandbox, controlling security levels, token restrictions, job object settings, and access rules for sandboxed processes. It is forward-declared in `sandbox/win/src/sandbox.h`.\n\n3. **Renderer sandbox configuration (content/browser)**: Located in `content/browser/renderer_host/renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.cc`. The class `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate` configures sandbox parameters for renderer process launch. The key function `GetSandboxType()` returns `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox::kRenderer`, identifying this as a renderer sandbox. On Windows, additional policy configuration is applied via `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegateWin`.\n\n4. **SandboxType enum and sandbox profile mappings**: The `Sandbox` enum (which serves as the SandboxType) is defined in `sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom` — it enumerates all sandbox profiles including `kRenderer`, `kGpu`, `kNetwork`, `kService`, `kUtility`, etc. The mapping functions (e.g., `SandboxTypeFromCommandLine`, `SetCommandLineFlagsForSandboxType`) are declared in `sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h` and map between command-line flags and sandbox enum values."
